        'Image Resizer changes the width and height of an image to match profile photos, thumbnails, banners, product images, and upload requirements. It saves time when a platform expects a specific size.',
        'Keeping the original aspect ratio prevents stretched or distorted results. After resizing, check the final image in the place where it will be used to make sure it still looks sharp and correctly framed.',
        'Image Resizer covers every situation that requires a precise pixel size: social media profile photos such as Instagram 110×110 or YouTube channel art at 2560×1440, ecommerce product image standards, and presentation slide graphics. The resizer handles the conversion in the browser without needing a separate image editor.',
